    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I'm honestly a little heartbroken to be parting with this beauty, but it's time for someone else to enjoy it. This car is in absolutely pristine condition\u2014I\u2019ve babied it since the day I drove it off the lot! It has been kept in a climate-controlled garage and looks exactly like it did in the showroom. Not a single scratch, the interior is flawless, and it still has that wonderful new-car smell. It drives like an absolute dream! If you're looking for a ride that\u2019s been cared for with a ton of love, this is the one. Feel free to reach out\u2014I\u2019d love to chat and show it to you!",
      "price": 44900.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure VANOS system to deliver linear power up to an 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers precise gate engagement, paired with a factory M-Variable Lock differential for superior lateral grip. This chassis has undergone proactive subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive cooling system overhaul. The paint remains in concours state with zero swirling, while the interior retains its original matte finish on the Nappa leather bolsters. A documented, collector-tier example of BMW\u2019s finest naturally aspirated era.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used car. Mint condition. Garage kept. Clean title. No mechanical issues. Inspections welcome.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
